{
  "text": "Previous studies provided convincing evidence for local adaptation of Drosophila melanogaster, which originated in sub-Saharan Africa and subsequently colonized many parts of the world [CITATION_1] . They suggested that numerous beneficial mutations were fixed during the habitat expansion after the last glaciation (10,000 years ago; [CITATION_2] in the process of adapting to local environments [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
